{"version":1,"kind":"Article","sha256":"1b3885a1e4876f6e1eab64f0fa5713754c26fccf0a71911d2f8f860208cbbeb6","slug":"blog.2022.cloud-services-academia","location":"/blog/2022/cloud-services-academia.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Ask Twitter: Why don’t academic researchers use cloud services?","tags":["cloud"],"date":"2022-09-05","content_includes_title":false,"authors":[{"id":"chris","nameParsed":{"literal":"Chris Holdgraf","given":"Chris","family":"Holdgraf"},"name":"Chris Holdgraf","orcid":"0000-0002-2391-0678","affiliations":["affiliations-myst-generated-uid-0","affiliations-myst-generated-uid-1"],"twitter":"choldgraf","github":"choldgraf","url":"https://chrisholdgraf.com"}],"github":"https://github.com/choldgraf/choldgraf.github.io","affiliations":[{"name":"2i2c","url":"https://2i2c.org","id":"affiliations-myst-generated-uid-0"},{"name":"Project Jupyter","url":"https://jupyter.org","id":"affiliations-myst-generated-uid-1"}],"abbreviations":{"LF":"The Linux Foundation","JF":"The Jupyter Foundation","JEC":"Jupyter Executive Council","JFB":"The Jupyter Foundation Board","SSC":"Software Steering Council","OSPO":"Open Source Program Office"},"numbering":{"title":{"offset":2}},"edit_url":"https://github.com/choldgraf/choldgraf.github.io/blob/main/blog/2022/cloud-services-academia.md","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"cloud-services-academia.md","url":"/build/cloud-services-acade-01961107d327472cb4df275faace3f1b.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"this is an experiment at making my ","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"OOLza9qFZR"},{"type":"link","url":"https://twitter.com/choldgraf","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Twitter conversations","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"DHlwBrGj9B"}],"urlSource":"https://twitter.com/choldgraf","key":"WO7dPqTuvw"},{"type":"text","value":" a bit more useful and archivable over time. It’s going to be a bit messy and unpolished, but hopefully that makes it more likely I’ll actually do it :-)","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"tdwEfeXfZ9"}],"key":"dNSTxgAnsT"}],"key":"gxhdj75krl"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Over the past decade, cloud infrastructure has become increasingly popular in industry.\nAn ecosystem of modular tools and cloud services (often called ","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"eteMcACHcQ"},{"type":"link","url":"https://future.com/emerging-architectures-modern-data-infrastructure/","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"the Modern Data Stack","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"qPfSRHrX3H"}],"urlSource":"https://future.com/emerging-architectures-modern-data-infrastructure/","key":"WG0tEsCr0A"},{"type":"text","value":") has filled many data needs for companies.","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"hQonpZ3RfF"}],"key":"znQdjtn3I3"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"However, academic research and education still largely does not utilize this stack.\nInstead, they optimize for local workflows or shared infrastructure that exists on-premise.\nIf you believe (as I do) that cloud infrastructure has the potential to help people do work more effectively and collaboratively, then it’s important to understand why people don’t use these kinds of tools.","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"QiIsNbI9n8"}],"key":"DjOpZz4j2I"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, I decided to ask Twitter why academics tend to not utilize cloud infrastructure:","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"O0ZVRd1vpx"}],"key":"uRkUb3IMwb"},{"type":"link","url":"https://twitter.com/choldgraf/status/1564614538309390345","children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://​twitter​.com​/choldgraf​/status​/1564614538309390345","key":"aK1leKHcUA"}],"urlSource":"https://twitter.com/choldgraf/status/1564614538309390345","key":"CREAwUqC30"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Below is a brief summary of the major points that several people made.","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"key":"CO1nQvGWy8"}],"key":"j3wqGmNSmj"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Fear of high costs","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"VXBDSCm4o4"}],"identifier":"fear-of-high-costs","label":"Fear of high costs","html_id":"fear-of-high-costs","implicit":true,"key":"MqkFLka80o"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The most common challenge is the fear of over-running cloud costs.\nWith on-prem infrastructure, you pay for allotments of time up-front (or don’t pay at all).\nCloud infrastructure allows you to “pay as you go”, but this sometimes means ","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"RqNL0e4poS"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"over-paying","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"LIgxUJzZcv"}],"key":"urUCy60g4K"},{"type":"text","value":" if you used resources you didn’t expect:","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"R69ZoGv2AV"}],"key":"XuaRNrEOHJ"},{"type":"link","url":"https://twitter.com/anshulkundaje/status/1551585264262295552","children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://​twitter​.com​/anshulkundaje​/status​/1551585264262295552","key":"ifKK12XpXQ"}],"urlSource":"https://twitter.com/anshulkundaje/status/1551585264262295552","key":"RUpenMuRwn"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cost monitoring needs to be a more obvious part of cloud services","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"key":"SjV654bv5l"}],"key":"OVbIe4RPE7"},{"type":"text","value":".\nFortunately, most cloud providers have their own budgeting and cost monitoring services to prevent this from happening.\nHowever, these don’t seem to be well-understood or utilized.\nThat brings us to the next concern:","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"key":"A1qeHvr794"}],"key":"lG93NUce3Y"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":1},"end":{"line":40,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A confusing landscape of tools and services","position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":1},"end":{"line":40,"column":1}},"key":"SmlDONCebk"}],"identifier":"a-confusing-landscape-of-tools-and-services","label":"A confusing landscape of tools and services","html_id":"a-confusing-landscape-of-tools-and-services","implicit":true,"key":"aNlAzxLBbo"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":43,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"There are hundreds of cloud services for data workflows in existence.\nAll of them make one thing a little bit easier, but you still need knowledge to:","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"key":"kMtIeEvicK"}],"key":"Wd1uMRenAf"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":47,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Choose the right cloud services","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"key":"kYg3lsUgS6"}],"key":"AYm4ChWmkZ"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":47,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Integrate them together","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"key":"BLywGoyb2A"}],"key":"dcVqXMcnno"}],"key":"EWJZon1DJi"},{"type":"link","url":"https://twitter.com/cboettig/status/1564671199547838464","children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://​twitter​.com​/cboettig​/status​/1564671199547838464","key":"IpQ7aeENQL"}],"urlSource":"https://twitter.com/cboettig/status/1564671199547838464","key":"INY51qGbLf"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As a result, many cloud services that ","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"key":"QrRS3zzyfb"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"might","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"key":"GOGZP7RgfY"}],"key":"ESBmcYDOaW"},{"type":"text","value":" be useful are effectively not used because they get lost in all the noise out there.","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"key":"gR7ZsBqyK2"}],"key":"OKJ9jUFE8d"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":54,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In short, ","position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":53,"column":1}},"key":"KVDoeJtWus"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":53,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"researchers need support in navigating this space","position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":53,"column":1}},"key":"K6FmOsSS2P"}],"key":"DT7MvHfJAI"},{"type":"text","value":".\nThey need organizations to understand their workflows and recommend a few specific things to use instead of exposing them to the hundreds of options out there.","position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":53,"column":1}},"key":"aLdVLvVuHM"}],"key":"BrCXSGkPAg"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"High start-up costs and no DevOps experience","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"key":"hqs4ZKF8s1"}],"identifier":"high-start-up-costs-and-no-devops-experience","label":"High start-up costs and no DevOps experience","html_id":"high-start-up-costs-and-no-devops-experience","implicit":true,"key":"Uy4y5Wrr5g"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":60,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Even if you ","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"key":"ucIup3K2wj"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"do","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"key":"Ewj91fga6i"}],"key":"PNNQah4fyG"},{"type":"text","value":" find the set of services that you want, you need some way to expose these services to your collaborators or research group.\nYou also need to manage this integration over time as things change, break, etc.\nUniversity groups often do not have dedicated cloud expertise, and so this lands at the feet of post-docs and graduate students with energy and interest to try things out.","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"key":"pIV41HwoC1"}],"key":"rfEoT5SHEj"},{"type":"link","url":"https://twitter.com/ixek/status/1565645082275057664","children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://​twitter​.com​/ixek​/status​/1565645082275057664","key":"fV8srrfVj3"}],"urlSource":"https://twitter.com/ixek/status/1565645082275057664","key":"T9jtfeZEi5"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"However, asking a student to learn and run your cloud infrastructure is also a risky move.\nStudents move on, and DevOps skills are in high demand.\nWhat happens if you lose that person, or if your grant runs out?","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":65,"column":1}},"key":"Vw7lRtiFc9"}],"key":"IUwr9SFp3F"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":71,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Researchers need others to manage cloud infrastructure for them","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"key":"SnrrDeaLfM"}],"key":"V7BYDUugFS"},{"type":"text","value":".\nIntegrating and using most services still requires expertise similar to a systems administrator (but now with cloud infrastructure as well).\nWe need more services that manage this complexity for them.","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"key":"z6jR0wi7OH"}],"key":"A4CXUCPqWw"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pain to first compute is higher for cloud","position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"key":"COkodvC4He"}],"identifier":"pain-to-first-compute-is-higher-for-cloud","label":"Pain to first compute is higher for cloud","html_id":"pain-to-first-compute-is-higher-for-cloud","implicit":true,"key":"GNA0QAlwd0"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Universities recognize that managed services are useful to research - they just prioritize on-premises infrastructure over everything else.\nFor example, many people noted that HPC is more heavily used simply because the university puts most of their resources into easing the use of this infrastructure.","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"key":"cDAlgEzHyG"}],"key":"w2woU5RItE"},{"type":"link","url":"https://twitter.com/SpectralFilter/status/1564697622660763648","children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://​twitter​.com​/SpectralFilter​/status​/1564697622660763648","key":"tEyoynpOMG"}],"urlSource":"https://twitter.com/SpectralFilter/status/1564697622660763648","key":"AgHtnoK0TJ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Universities need to invest in lowering the energy barrier to cloud services as well as on-prem infrastructure","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"key":"UksC2gglHJ"}],"key":"Uafkm2ZDyE"},{"type":"text","value":". We don’t want universities to divest from all of their on-prem hardware and services, but we should make at least marginal investments in similarly reducing the barriers to using cloud infrastructure. What would it look like if universities made it as easy to set up and pay for cloud infrastructure as they do for HPC? I bet a lot more people would experiment and learn with the cloud.","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"key":"PMvj2CKdML"}],"key":"mbKb6Zpmnr"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":83,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Continuity of service / lock-in concerns","position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":83,"column":1}},"key":"nwMFpxEhVc"}],"identifier":"continuity-of-service-lock-in-concerns","label":"Continuity of service / lock-in concerns","html_id":"continuity-of-service-lock-in-concerns","implicit":true,"key":"B4wPnUMdLS"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":86,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When you’re relying on a service exposed by some other organization, you must hope that the service continues to be useful.\nMany academics have been burned when services discontinue.","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"key":"AQKWQpp1DA"}],"key":"ADkUXCBpdb"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":88,"column":1},"end":{"line":88,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This might happen for a number of reasons:","position":{"start":{"line":88,"column":1},"end":{"line":88,"column":1}},"key":"o0qGfNYnTd"}],"key":"DNC8KXUpjd"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":90,"column":1},"end":{"line":95,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":90,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"An ","position":{"start":{"line":90,"column":1},"end":{"line":90,"column":1}},"key":"zvl2CFCD0v"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":90,"column":1},"end":{"line":90,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"internal service","position":{"start":{"line":90,"column":1},"end":{"line":90,"column":1}},"key":"ht4U9Zg2ra"}],"key":"XQArpqDzcf"},{"type":"text","value":" discontinues because the organization no-longer has capacity to manage it themselves. This is particularly challenging in the context of research funding, which tends to be “boom or bust”.\nYou get a grant and are well-funded for 3 years.\nAfter it runs out, maybe you’ve got a few months of a gap without dedicated resources for infrastructure.\nWhat happens if your DevOps person’s salary depends on that grant?","position":{"start":{"line":90,"column":1},"end":{"line":90,"column":1}},"key":"Y67eOi4zZA"}],"key":"nlzVbvoDYU"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":95,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"An ","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"key":"o67AjxfG18"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"external service","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"key":"c1BxQSR9K8"}],"key":"NzbIKM5kCA"},{"type":"text","value":" discontinues because the organization running it pivoted to a new model or cost structure. This is challenging because many cloud services are designed for enterprise, the research community. They are also not accountible to the research community, and do not give it direct representation or governing power over the direction of the services.","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"key":"wk5U13aCrW"}],"key":"WtLWzaQJV7"}],"key":"KLtLjinxBP"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Moreover, when our workflows are not easily portable, it creates extra switching cost and strain on a researcher’s workflow.\nMany services (both external and internal) do not properly leverage pre-existing and modular tools to make it easy to switch (and why would they, if they’re optimizing for their own growth over the growth of the ecosystem).","position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"key":"xDcJSlNcz5"}],"key":"h8f1f1SLnQ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":101,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":99,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Researchers need cost-sharing mechanisms for cloud infrastructure that is designed for them","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":99,"column":1}},"key":"tdEvIXzxHA"}],"key":"Ib1DNBHKaZ"},{"type":"text","value":".\nThis would allow them to pool their resources and ensure continuity and quality of service without relying on boom and bust cycles of single grants.","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":99,"column":1}},"key":"LjsxQ7oaII"},{"type":"footnoteReference","identifier":"funding-ideas","label":"funding-ideas","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":99,"column":1}},"enumerator":"1","key":"He8aZgAdBa"},{"type":"text","value":"\nIt would also allow them to support reliable and sustainable services that are designed for the unique problems that the research community has (like being a huge, globally-distributed, heterogeneous community with almost no top-down control and thousands of different workflows).","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":99,"column":1}},"key":"TS4meOkAMM"}],"key":"DB4VKM6q9x"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":105,"column":1},"end":{"line":105,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Wrap-up: we need more cloud-native services for research","position":{"start":{"line":105,"column":1},"end":{"line":105,"column":1}},"key":"iq8rGVMEXE"}],"identifier":"wrap-up-we-need-more-cloud-native-services-for-research","label":"Wrap-up: we need more cloud-native services for research","html_id":"wrap-up-we-need-more-cloud-native-services-for-research","implicit":true,"key":"CnThUKBcKZ"},{"ty